  "prompt": "Who sets the price for games on Steam?",
  "response": "The price for games on Steam is primarily set by the game's publisher or developer. They decide the initial price point as well as any discounts or sales promotions. Valve, the company that owns Steam, provides some guidelines and tools for pricing, but ultimately, the decision is up to those who own the rights to the game. Valve may influence pricing through platform-wide sales events, but these are typically opt-in for individual developers and publishers.",
